Path: This week in Nu #19
Content:
Happy Nu year!
We wrote up a 
[link: https://www.nushell.sh/blog/2019/12/31/happy-nu-year-2020.html] year-in-review post
notryanb added a new 
``uniq``
 command (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1132] #1132
)
quebin31 updated some of our internal structures names to be more consistent (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1133] #1133
)
andrasio refactored some plugin code and continued to improve tests (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1135] #1135
)
miller-time fixed how Nu handled single-quotes in external commands (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1139] #1139
)
vorot93 and jonathandturner finished the move to using clippy, which is now enabled on CI (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1136] #1136
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1142] #1142
)
Aloso added support for moving a word-at-a-time with ctrl-left and ctrl-right (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1141] #1141
)
avendesa replaced the 
``which``
 command with an upgraded version (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1144] #1144
)
jonathandturner has been improving stability and removing unwraps, going from 204 to 86 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1147] #1147
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1148] #1148
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1149] #1149
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1150] #1150
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1152] #1152
)
